intro: Seseli quinquefolium, commonly known as five-leaved seseli, is a flowering plant native to parts of Europe and Asia. It belongs to the Apiaceae family, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided leaves and small, clustered flowers. The plant typically grows in open, sunny habitats such as grasslands and rocky areas. It produces small, white or greenish flowers that bloom in late spring to early summer. Seseli quinquefolium is often found in disturbed soils and is considered a herbaceous perennial.
